                <p> <note>Latin</note><ref target="https://godot.date/id/q8tzTG5MBsGJyh6JvYjDqE"> Nero Claudius Drusus Caesar Augustus Germanicus Imperator</ref> made roads through the agency of Lucius Pedius Blaesus, proconsul of Crete and Cyrene
</p>
            <p><note>Greek</note> Nero Claudius Drusus Caesar Augustus Germanicus Imperator made roads through the agency of Lucius Pedius Blaesus, proconsul of Crete and Cyrene</p></div></div>
            
            <div type="commentary">
                <head>Commentary</head>
                <p>Lines 1-3: The titulature suggests the first months of Nero’s reign</p>
                <p>Lines 5 (and 13): Pedius Blaesus (<title>PIR<hi rend="superscript">2</hi></title>, P 0212, Thomassen, <title><ref target="http://www.isvroma.it/public/Publications/laterculi.pdf">Laterculi</ref></title> 38.023) 
                    is on record in Tacitus, <title>Annales</title> 14.18 (available at <ref target=" http://data.perseus.org/citations/urn:cts:latinLit:phi1351.phi005.perseus-lat1:14.18">Perseus</ref>) and 
                    Hist. 1.77.6 (available at <ref target="http://data.perseus.org/citations/urn:cts:latinLit:phi1351.phi004.perseus-lat1:1.77">Perseus</ref>) as a proconsul prosecuted by Cyrene and 
                    condemned for extortion in 59 CE but reinstated by Otho.</p> 
                <p> Line 16: The mileage figure may have been 7 or 8 in the light of the distance from Cyrene</p>
                <!-- <p> Claudius was apparently the first Roman ruler to set up milestones in Cyrenaica </p> -->
            </div>
